cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.IR 

This paper deals with natural language argumentation and reasoning, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The methodology developed for reconstructing warrants involves crowdsourcing and scalability, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of common sense in comprehending arguments also indicates a potential connection to cognitive science (cs.CY). Finally, the task of choosing the correct implicit warrant from two options involves language understanding and information retrieval, which could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR).
